articles.author: Rick Neale
articles.title: Axiom-3 all-European private astronaut mission to launch Wednesday - Florida Today
articles.description: A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket will launch the four astronauts and their SpaceX Dragon spacecraft from pad 39A at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center.
articles.content:
Nicknamed Axiom-3, the first all-European private astronaut mission to the International Space Station is targeting 5:11 p.m. EST Wednesday for launch from NASA's Kennedy Space Center.
